history.content:
Hey all, Web Design DeCal enrollment applications are open! If you'd like to audit, there is no need to apply. We'll post recorded lectures on YouTube and you'll have access to course materials.

You know you're going to spend the Fall semester surfing the internet, especially when it's remote — why not spend some of this time learning how to make beautifully designed websites too? Come take the Web Design DeCal and learn to design and code a website from scratch!

Learn more at wdd.io and check out some awesome projects from past students at webdesigndecal.github.io/showcase.

This 2-unit course will be held on Tuesdays 7:00 – 8:30 PM and Thursdays 7:00 – 8:00 PM PDT online (Zoom).

Apply at wdd.io/go/apply by Saturday, August 29th 11:59 PM (PDT). This class is designed for beginners and all majors, no prior coding experience necessary. Hope to see you in class!
